cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as topic models and word embeddings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses learning hidden semantic representations using probabilistic models and neural networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the learned embeddings on word and document similarity tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a relevant category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to learn interpretable embeddings. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper employs multimodal regularization to learn embeddings for other modalities such as timestamps and categories.
